<snippet>
	<content><![CDATA[


* Routers in the backbone area (Area 0) are called backbone routers.

* Routers between 2 areas (one interface must be on Area 0) are called Area Border Routers (ABR)

* Routers that run OSPF on one interface and Other routing protocol like RIP on other interface and redistributing routes is called ASBR.

]]></content>
